               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17700221-14-person145">
                  Sam.
                   Belas
               <interp inst="t17700221-14-person145" type="surname" value="Belas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17700221-14-person145" type="given" value="Sam."></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17700221-14-person145" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I met the prisoner between three and four o'clock that morning, in Pick-ax-street, with a new board on his shoulder. I suspected he had stole it from this new building in Fan's-alley. I went there to see, and found a breach made, and another board loose. I put out my candle, and watched to see if any body would come for that. The prisoner came back in order to take it, and I stopped him. I got him into an alehouse, under<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177002210009"></xptr> pretence to give him some purl, and sent for the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>The boards were my own I had a little jobb to do in the neighbourhood, and was carrying them in order to do it.</p>
